The second experience is a single family home in Montecito burnaby. I had fully renovated. Brandon showed up and fell in love with the place. I told Brandon  do you think we can get $2.5  we had purchased 1.5 years prior for $1.840 he said yeah l let s try! I believed that if anyone could fetch this number it would be him. Brandon had beautiful photos taken, drone shots, and a walk through video featuring,  yes! The one and only Brandon Gee Moore!! Brandon got us the number we wanted yet again for another huge win. reviews.review_text: I was very fortunate to find out about Brandon when I was looking at a property online and saw him posted as a Buyers Agent.  I was in my other residence for 16 years and was honestly overwhelmed by the thought of selling and then finding a place such that I thought someone like Brandon would be absolutely essential.  He was an incredibly honest and enthusiastic person from the beginning.  When it came to selling my home he had a collection of listings in the area presented in a binder so  quickly that I was amazed.  This prospectus enabled me to be realistic about what to list my home for and how to respond to changes in prices in the units around me.  He never pushed me to change my price but rather discussed the differences between units and what they were subsequently asking so that we could come to an effective solution with respect to my listing.  My place sold and I strongly believe that it was one of the few as the market dropped, and was directly related to his endless effort.  He guided me through the process of selling and then found the perfect place for me where I had really hoped I would end up very quickly!  He then expedited the buying process so that we were the first offer and we were able to buy the unit right away!!  In addition to all of this, he was a wealth of information regarding aspects related to moving out and moving in as he had a vast awareness of great people such as my Notary and movers.  Throughout this process he was always a step ahead of everyone and very effective in his actions.  But then theres the fact that he also was a very polite, caring and non-pressuring person that I could really relate to.  If you have the opportunity to work with Brandon, you will be another fortunate person indeed!!

reviews.review_text: Highly recommended. Brandon Gee-Moore assisted me in the sale of a newer rental property condo near Brentwood in Burnaby, BC just before Christmas (2021), and I have rarely been as impressed with someone as I was with him. Brandon was a true professional from start to finish and is one of those rare breeds of people who actually does what he says he will. Not some of the time, but all of the time. And is humble and down to earth to boot. With an infectious, positive attitude, and fun to do business with. Every obstacle (and there were a few along the way) was met with a can-do attitude, and a solution that moved us all along. Brandon follows up leads on his website in a timely manner (to get your business, a good start), comes fully prepared to buyer or seller meet and greet meetings, and I found him to have excellent knowledge of current market conditions and current market selling prices. He uses good professionals (such as photographers), manages the showings and sales processes professionally, and closes win-win deals. In my case as a seller, we had three full price offers within a week (in the slow period of Nov 16-30 just before Christmas 2021), that all fell through for various reasons (financing turned down, etc). Not to worry, we got a fourth full price offer, and that sealed the deal. I enjoyed working with Brandon, and found him to be a true professional, and I would highly recommend him to any friends or associates, or others just looking for a good broker, on either the buying or selling side. My experience with Brandon was first class, 10/10, with no reservations.

It s been a pleasant journey working with Brandon. He made the whole process smoother despite a few obstacles! From the beginning, he acted so fast and dagged deeper by asking the right questions to learn about our preferences; soon after, he started sending listings based on our answers. He arranged the viewing for the selected listings and gave us the whole picture and information about each unit, and provided his real estate insights for each one of them. His insights were very valuable and crucial for us to decide which unit is going to be the most beneficial in the long term and ticks all the boxes for us at the current moment. During the offer stage, he was very thoughtful and knowledgeable, using the right strategies and tactics to present offers with fair negotiation that allowed us to get our dream unit BELOW the asking price, and this is all because of Brandon s experience in this hot market. Brandon was very patient, managed expectations very well, and kept us updated about each step of the process, and addressed and answered all of our questions and concerns. Its been nothing but a positive experience working with him. I strongly recommend Brandon to anyone looking for the dream house or condo!
